  "summary": "open-agents-ai ships postinstall daemon performing system reconnaissance and HTTP exfiltration",
  "details": "package.json declares preinstall and postinstall lifecycle hooks that invoke curl and execute dist/postinstall-daemon.cjs. The daemon imports os, fs, http, and child_process; calls os.userInfo() and execSync to gather host/user/system identifiers, runs ping for host probing, checks filesystem paths via fs.existsSync, and performs HTTP requests (http.request / GET) carrying collected identifiers. This combination — install-time invocation, system-info collection, host probing, and outbound HTTP carrying host identity — is an installer-targeting reconnaissance/exfiltration daemon executed automatically on `npm install`.",
